listitem.para:
If A and B are of different integer encoding,
integer promotion is performed according to the following rules:


        if any operand is unsigned, int_res is unsigned;


        int_res has the encoding of the higher number of bits between the encoding of A and B;


        A and B are promoted to the same encoding before computation is performed

refsection.programlisting:
A = [0 1; 1 0];
B = [1 1; 0 0];
spA = sparse(A);
spB = sparse(B);
spbA = sparse(A<>0);
spbB = sparse(B<>0);
iA = int8(A);
iB = int8(B);
cA = A + 0*%i;
cB = B + 0*%i;

// A is evaluated as
// [%f, %t;
//  %t, %f]
// B is evaluated as
// [%t, %t;
//  %f, %f]

// & as logical operation
A & B
A & spB  // Result is sparse encoded
iA & spB // Result is sparse encoded
cA & iB

// & as bitwise operation
iA & iB

i8_A = int8([ -1, 1; 127, -128]);
// Integer representation of i8_A:
// [ 1111 1111, 0000 0001 ;
//   0111 1111, 1000 0000 ]

i8_B = int8([-2, 0; 126, -127]);
// Integer representation of i8_A:
// [ 1111 1110, 0000 0000 ;
//   0111 1110, 1000 0001 ]

i8_1 & i8_B

// Integer promotion
i16_A = int16(i8_A);
ui32_B = uint32(i8_B);

i16_A & ui32_B

// && as a shortcut operation
function res = foo()
    disp("this is executed");
    res = %t;
endfunction

if ( %f & foo() ) then
    // This is not executed
end

A && foo()  // A has at least one element equals to 0
iA && foo() // therefore, foo() is not executed
cA && foo()

iA && iB // iA is evalueated as false resulting in the short-circuited operation
